1
00:00:23,565 --> 00:00:25,317
[woman on TV] <i>After the attack</i>
<i>at the</i> Bulletin

2
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:27,611
<i>and the horrible tragedy</i>
<i>at the Clinton Church,</i>

3
00:00:27,694 --> 00:00:31,698
<i>what will it take before people realize</i>
<i>that Wilson Fisk was set up by Daredevil?</i>

4
00:00:31,782 --> 00:00:35,369
[man] <i>People are beginning to realize</i>
<i>Fisk was the victim of a smear campaign.</i>

5
00:00:35,452 --> 00:00:37,871
<i>Daredevil was the one behind it all.</i>

6
00:00:37,955 --> 00:00:41,416
<i>And what about Daredevil's apologists</i>
<i>like Blake Tower and Karen Page?</i>

7
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,669
-[woman] <i>She should be in jail.</i>
<i>-</i>[man] <i>We have breaking news</i>

8
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:47,130
<i>that Fisk has invited</i>
<i>many of New York's most powerful figures</i>

9
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:50,717
<i>to the Presidential Hotel</i>
<i>for some kind of surprise announcement.</i>

10
00:00:50,801 --> 00:00:51,635
[woman] <i>Oh.</i>

11
00:00:58,976 --> 00:01:02,145
[panting] Kidnapping me
will get you nothing.

12
00:01:02,229 --> 00:01:04,273
-What is Fisk planning?
-Planning?

13
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:07,734
I scouted his hotel. Extra security.

14
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:10,904
Preparations for some big event.
What is it?

15
00:01:10,988 --> 00:01:13,365
What Fisk will do to me
is infinitely worse--

16
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:14,700
[Matt grunts]

17
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:18,495
Things are about to get very bad for you.

18
00:01:19,371 --> 00:01:23,458
What is Fisk planning?

19
00:01:23,542 --> 00:01:24,918
Do you mind if I come in?

20
00:01:31,049 --> 00:01:32,134
[Fisk gasps softly]

21
00:01:32,926 --> 00:01:33,927
Marriage?

22
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:35,721
He's been planning the ceremony
for months.

23
00:01:35,804 --> 00:01:41,059
He's gonna charm the press and the public
and make Hell's Kitchen love him again.

24
00:01:42,352 --> 00:01:46,565
-Do I look that nervous?
-Yes, a little, but it's charming.

25
00:01:56,575 --> 00:02:00,704
I never knew that I could feel this way
until the day that we met.

26
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:04,458
I didn't think that I was capable,

27
00:02:05,042 --> 00:02:06,835
that there would be someone...

28
00:02:09,171 --> 00:02:11,882
that I would care for
more than my own life.

29
00:02:13,258 --> 00:02:17,554
That her happiness would be
more important than anything else.

30
00:02:18,263 --> 00:02:19,264
And then...

31
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:28,774
a terrifying thought occurred to me
that perhaps my feelings were a trick.

32
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:32,444
The self-deception of a vain man.

33
00:02:35,072 --> 00:02:36,531
That the only reason why I love you

34
00:02:36,615 --> 00:02:39,576
is because of the way
I see my reflection in your eyes.

35
00:02:41,286 --> 00:02:44,122
That thought, it fills me with dread.

36
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,751
The fear that...

37
00:02:50,045 --> 00:02:51,672
that I don't deserve you...

38
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:54,800
and that I am broken.

39
00:02:57,344 --> 00:02:59,680
Don't you understand we're all broken?

40
00:03:00,764 --> 00:03:05,477
The point is to find the person
whose broken pieces fit with yours.

41
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:08,772
[Matt] <i>You're gonna tell me everything.</i>

42
00:03:08,855 --> 00:03:12,067
I wanna know where everyone is gonna be.

43
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:15,070
Anyone who could stop me.

44
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:16,446
Stop you?

45
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:18,240
From killing Fisk.

46
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:22,744
He controls all of the FBI agents
who are guarding him.

47
00:03:22,828 --> 00:03:24,204
The hotel is a fortress.

48
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:25,288
Is that a no?

49
00:03:26,081 --> 00:03:28,083
-You'll never get to him.
-Sounds like a no.

50
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:31,795
[Felix screaming]

51
00:03:31,878 --> 00:03:33,797
[wailing]

52
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,512
I can give you something better!

53
00:03:41,555 --> 00:03:42,806
I'm listening.

54
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:48,687
I witnessed Ms. Marianna
order the murder of Agent Nadeem.

55
00:03:50,981 --> 00:03:52,941
And Fisk ordered many.

56
00:03:54,109 --> 00:03:57,028
Agent Winn. Julie Barnes!

57
00:03:57,112 --> 00:03:59,114
I could testify!

58
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,533
I know about Winn and Nadeem.

59
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,161
Who's Julie Barnes?

60
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:10,167
The rose.

61
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,170
I think.

62
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:37,027
[theme music playing]

63
00:05:41,758 --> 00:05:44,219
Tell me again
how you ended up dangling off a building?

64
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,012
I tripped.

65
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:48,431
Get him out of here.

66
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,900
I thought "ambulance chaser"
was a figure of speech.

67
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,403
Not one of your best burns, Detective.

68
00:06:01,945 --> 00:06:03,530
I'm not in the mood to be clever today.

69
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:05,156
Yeah, me neither.

70
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,242
We had him, Foggy.

71
00:06:08,535 --> 00:06:10,203
We were this goddamn close.

72
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:11,705
I know.

73
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:15,584
Instead of locking up that bald asshole,

74
00:06:15,667 --> 00:06:18,378
I had to tell Mrs. Nadeem
she'd never see her husband again.

75
00:06:18,461 --> 00:06:19,504
How did that happen?

76
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:21,631
I don't know.

77
00:06:24,009 --> 00:06:25,010
Listen.

78
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:27,929
Something's been brought to my attention.

79
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:32,225
As an officer of the court,
I'm compelled to report it.

80
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:35,270
I have reason to believe

81
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:38,189
that someone's gonna try
to murder Wilson Fisk today.

82
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:39,274
Someone, huh?

83
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:43,194
About what time is this going down?
I wanna have some popcorn ready.

84
00:06:43,278 --> 00:06:45,655
Need I remind you
of your obligation to protect and serve?

85
00:06:45,739 --> 00:06:47,824
Stick your obligation up your ass, Nelson.

86
00:06:49,242 --> 00:06:51,953
If Fisk disappears,
all his bullshit goes with him.

87
00:06:52,037 --> 00:06:56,124
And the FBI agents on his payroll
just fold back into the mix.

88
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:59,044
Including the one who shot Ray.

89
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:02,339
Don't think of it as protecting Fisk.

90
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,591
Think of it as protecting
the case we can build

91
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,593
against the shitbags who helped him.

92
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:09,304
Once we get them,
they'll turn faster than old milk.

93
00:07:09,387 --> 00:07:13,016
Still, with Fisk gone,
we'll get 'em eventually.

94
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:16,186
Brett, please.

95
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:19,272
This certain someone
we're talking about...

96
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:22,317
he's angry.

97
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:27,405
But I know he'll do the right thing
if I can just slow him down.

98
00:07:28,031 --> 00:07:29,574
Give him time to think.

99
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:34,955
I'll beef up the perimeter
around the hotel.

100
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:38,625
-But I'm sending in my C team.
-Thank you.

101
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:40,752
I'm talking rookies and retirees.

102
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,466
[Hattley] After the body
of Supervisory Special Agent Winn

103
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:47,968
was found in the Hudson,

104
00:07:48,051 --> 00:07:51,054
search divers also recovered
the murder weapon.

105
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:55,976
The registered service sidearm
of fellow FBI agent Ray Nadeem.

106
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:59,521
When agents went
to take Nadeem into custody,

107
00:07:59,604 --> 00:08:01,606
he drew a weapon to resist arrest

108
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:04,818
and forced his fellow agents
to kill him in self-defense.

109
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:07,946
<i>Sadly, we may never know</i>
<i>what kind of mental instability</i>

110
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:11,157
<i>drove Ray Nadeem</i>
<i>to commit this senseless act.</i>

111
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:15,578
<i>But our thoughts and prayers go out</i>
<i>to the families of all the agents</i>

112
00:08:15,662 --> 00:08:17,497
<i>who have been impacted by these events.</i>

113
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:21,584
Press is calling me a liar.
FBI is calling Ray mentally unstable.

114
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:22,711
[scoffs]

115
00:08:23,294 --> 00:08:25,505
Ray's grand jury testimony is sealed,

116
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:29,884
so Fisk is just throwing up smokescreens
until people forget and move on.

117
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:30,885
Yeah?

118
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:33,388
Well, unless Matt figures out
some way to stop him,

119
00:08:33,471 --> 00:08:35,974
he's going to get away with it.
With all of it.

120
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,892
You mean unless Matt kills him.

121
00:08:40,103 --> 00:08:41,604
Shouldn't have warned Mahoney.

122
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:44,649
If the police have Fisk surrounded,

123
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:46,693
maybe Matt won't be able
to go through with it.

124
00:08:46,776 --> 00:08:49,487
Or maybe he'll get arrested. Or worse.

125
00:08:49,571 --> 00:08:50,405
Karen--

126
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:53,658
Look, I'm not saying that I want
him to kill Fisk. I don't want that.

127
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:57,996
What if it's the only way?

128
00:08:58,830 --> 00:09:01,666
It's, uh... It's not murder
if it's self-defense, right?

129
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:05,795
Technically, plotting to kill someone is
the exact legal opposite of self-defense.

130
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:07,255
You know what I mean.

131
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:10,592
I get it.

132
00:09:11,176 --> 00:09:14,763
Our best shot at taking down Fisk
died with Nadeem.

133
00:09:16,139 --> 00:09:18,558
But yesterday was also a good day...

134
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:21,352
-[Karen sighs]
-...because Matt came back to us.

135
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,104
The real Matt.

136
00:09:23,188 --> 00:09:24,814
Yeah, for, like, a minute maybe.

137
00:09:24,898 --> 00:09:27,275
Eventually, he'll come to his senses.

138
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:31,237
Matt's Matt because he believes that
everyone deserves a shot at redemption.

139
00:09:31,321 --> 00:09:32,489
Except Fisk.

140
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:35,700
Everyone. It's a Catholic thing.

141
00:09:35,784 --> 00:09:37,535
That's why he doesn't kill people.

142
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,746
If he crosses that line...

143
00:09:41,122 --> 00:09:43,625
Matt will never be able
to forgive himself.

144
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:48,254
And being around us will just remind him
of who he was and what he's done.

145
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:52,801
-Yeah, we'd really lose him, wouldn't we?
-Forever, this time.

146
00:09:57,472 --> 00:09:59,349
[cell phone vibrating]

147
00:10:00,308 --> 00:10:01,559
[sighs]

148
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:05,188
Hello?

149
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:09,818
Yes.

150
00:10:10,819 --> 00:10:12,320
Can I ask why?

151
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:15,949
Uh, no need. I know where you are.

152
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,368
What? What is it?

153
00:10:18,451 --> 00:10:19,577
[sighs]

154
00:10:20,662 --> 00:10:22,330
The FBI wants me to come in.

155
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,209
It's Fisk.

156
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:29,712
-Yeah. It might be.
-Might be?

157
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,632
Foggy, you're not going down there.

158
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,886
I have a life.

159
00:10:38,263 --> 00:10:40,306
I'm not prepared
to become a wanted fugitive.

160
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,850
Wait, wait, wait. No, just wait.

161
00:10:42,684 --> 00:10:45,645
What if it's a trap
and you don't walk out again? Huh?

162
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:50,483
Can you run that downstairs?

163
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:58,116
Mr. Nelson.

164
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:00,326
Special Agent Poindexter.

165
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:02,912
You just won me 50 bucks.

166
00:11:02,996 --> 00:11:05,331
Some of the guys
were betting you wouldn't show.

167
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:08,501
I'm always available to help the FBI,
Agent Poindexter.

168
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,295
In fact...

169
00:11:12,797 --> 00:11:13,798
please smile.

170
00:11:17,719 --> 00:11:18,720
There.

171
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:21,097
Posted to my campaign web page

172
00:11:21,181 --> 00:11:25,018
and the tens of thousands of
police officers that know that I'm here.

173
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,228
With you. Helping.

174
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:30,565
Relax, Mr. Nelson.
You're not in any danger.

175
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:33,193
You'll be very useful
when you're the next district attorney.

176
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:36,321
Why am I here?

177
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:40,450
-'Cause Ray Nadeem was a friend of yours.
-A client.

178
00:11:41,201 --> 00:11:43,411
Sad, the way it all turned out.

179
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:44,913
Even though he's dead,

180
00:11:44,996 --> 00:11:47,749
I can't answer any questions
that would violate privilege.

181
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,125
I'm not asking you to.

182
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:51,044
Follow me.

183
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,804
Thank you for coming, Mr. Nelson.

184
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:07,936
Mrs. Nadeem. What are you doing here?

185
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,521
I came to apologize.

186
00:12:11,105 --> 00:12:13,358
To apologize?

187
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:16,736
I asked them to call you,
because you were Ray's lawyer.

188
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:20,615
And I want to fully cooperate
with the investigation of my husband.

189
00:12:21,783 --> 00:12:23,117
What Ray did is...

190
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:27,121
How could a man I loved
with all my heart...

191
00:12:28,414 --> 00:12:32,335
the father of my son,
turn out to be such a monster?

192
00:12:32,835 --> 00:12:34,462
[Dex] It wasn't your fault, Seema.

193
00:12:34,545 --> 00:12:36,422
Ray fooled a lot of people.

194
00:12:36,965 --> 00:12:38,925
Nobody here blames you or Sami.

195
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:41,552
You're still part of the FBI family.

196
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:45,348
We'll give you the room.
Take all the time you need.

197
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:55,191
Suck it up.

198
00:12:55,275 --> 00:12:57,277
I'm only doing this because I have to.

199
00:13:00,321 --> 00:13:02,365
-How's Sami?
-He's okay.

200
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,033
With my sister.

201
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:06,327
I haven't told him yet.

202
00:13:07,036 --> 00:13:10,748
-When did you get here?
-I came as soon as I saw the news.

203
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:16,921
I didn't want to believe it,
but I know I needed to hear the truth.

204
00:13:22,385 --> 00:13:24,470
I'm so sorry. That...

205
00:13:25,722 --> 00:13:27,181
must have been an incredible shock.

206
00:13:27,265 --> 00:13:28,266
It was.

207
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:34,897
But I decided it was the right thing
for me to come in and to cooperate.

208
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:37,191
That was smart.

209
00:13:37,817 --> 00:13:39,485
Totally the right thing to do.

210
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:46,743
I was hoping you could help me
figure out how I can help the FBI.

211
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:50,747
And whether or not Ray's
life insurance policy will still pay.

212
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:53,166
Otherwise, Sami and I
have nothing to live on.

213
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,917
How will we survive?

214
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:06,471
I'll help you figure it out, Mrs. Nadeem.

215
00:14:07,430 --> 00:14:10,808
Whatever I can do
to help you and Sami get through this.

216
00:14:20,401 --> 00:14:21,569
[cell phone vibrating]

217
00:14:24,781 --> 00:14:26,115
What do you want?

218
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:29,494
[Matt over cell phone]
<i>I'm coming for you, Dex. And my suit.</i>

219
00:14:30,745 --> 00:14:31,746
Where's Felix?

220
00:14:32,163 --> 00:14:33,664
You'll find out soon enough.

221
00:14:33,748 --> 00:14:36,459
[Dex] <i>I've got some free time now.</i>
<i>Why don't we meet up?</i>

222
00:14:36,542 --> 00:14:37,627
I have a question.

223
00:14:38,920 --> 00:14:41,756
Did you enjoy the feeling you got
when you killed those birdies?

224
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,217
<i>Is that why you're still killing?</i>

225
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,510
Birdies?

226
00:14:45,593 --> 00:14:47,178
<i>The ones you killed with rocks.</i>

227
00:14:48,179 --> 00:14:49,931
<i>I bet it felt good at first, right?</i>

228
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:52,934
Then it's never the same after that.

229
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:57,355
What do you think Dr. Mercer would say
if she could see you now?

230
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:58,940
Can you hang on a second?

231
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:03,027
I need a tissue for all the tears
I'm crying over my shitty childhood.

232
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,614
Have you heard
from your friend Julie lately?

233
00:15:07,198 --> 00:15:09,492
You wanna talk to Dr. Mercer, asshole?
Keep talking.

234
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:12,537
What do you think she'd say if she knew
about the innocent people you killed?

235
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:15,748
I bet she'd be disappointed, Dex.

236
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,876
<i>If she were still alive.</i>

237
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:21,212
If you...

238
00:15:22,588 --> 00:15:24,132
If you hurt Julie--

239
00:15:24,215 --> 00:15:26,843
<i>Fisk had her killed.</i>

240
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:32,598
<i>He killed Julie, so he could replace her</i>
<i>as your North Star.</i>

241
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:38,563
You should stick
to beating on people in alleys,

242
00:15:39,230 --> 00:15:41,274
because you're not
going to get in my head.

243
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:42,900
<i>You don't have to believe me.</i>

244
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:45,945
Then again, you may wanna ask
how I got Manning's phone.

245
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:47,363
<i>Don't know. Don't care.</i>

246
00:15:48,197 --> 00:15:50,324
Julie wouldn't approve
of you killing people, Dex.

247
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:53,077
Stop saying her name.

248
00:15:53,161 --> 00:15:55,079
<i>You said you got some free time?</i>

249
00:15:56,456 --> 00:15:58,833
You may wanna check out 16 Canal Place.

250
00:15:59,375 --> 00:16:00,293
<i>Why?</i>

251
00:16:05,256 --> 00:16:10,136
<i>If you're showing this to Sami,</i>
<i>I need you to stop the video now.</i>

252
00:16:13,681 --> 00:16:14,807
<i>For everyone else...</i>

253
00:16:14,891 --> 00:16:18,186
<i>My name is Special Agent Ray Nadeem</i>
<i>of the FBI,</i>

254
00:16:18,269 --> 00:16:19,520
<i>and under federal law,</i>

255
00:16:19,604 --> 00:16:23,191
<i>I swear that the testimony</i>
<i>I'm about to give is the truth,</i>

256
00:16:23,274 --> 00:16:26,110
<i>whole truth</i>
<i>and nothing but the truth...</i>

257
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:29,113
<i>and should be considered</i>
<i>my dying declaration.</i>

258
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:34,702
<i>I'm guilty of a number of criminal acts,</i>
<i>and I was in no way acting alone.</i>

259
00:16:35,286 --> 00:16:40,333
Wilson Fisk coerced me
and a number of fellow FBI agents

260
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:43,169
into aiding and abetting
a criminal conspiracy...

261
00:16:44,045 --> 00:16:47,256
<i>to extort protection money</i>
<i>from New York crime organizations.</i>

262
00:16:47,340 --> 00:16:49,926
I gotta hand it to you, Fisk.
You know how to put on a show.

263
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:56,265
<i>Agents Arinori, Johnson, Markham, Mockter,</i>
<i>O'Connor and Ramsey all took part</i>

264
00:16:56,349 --> 00:16:58,684
<i>and continue to act as Fisk's operatives</i>

265
00:16:58,768 --> 00:17:03,856
<i>under the orders of our boss,</i>
<i>Special Agent in Charge Tammy Hattley.</i>

266
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:07,568
<i>There may be others. I can't be sure.</i>

267
00:17:07,652 --> 00:17:09,695
But I personally witnessed

268
00:17:09,779 --> 00:17:14,659
SAC Hattley murder Agent Winn
in her kitchen, using my handgun.

269
00:17:15,201 --> 00:17:16,786
-[gunshot]
-No!

270
00:17:16,869 --> 00:17:20,331
<i>And then witnessed Fisk's aide,</i>
<i>Felix Manning,</i>

271
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:24,961
<i>remove the body and use this crime</i>
<i>and threats against my family</i>

272
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:27,672
<i>to blackmail me</i>
<i>into cooperating with Fisk.</i>

273
00:17:28,256 --> 00:17:30,007
<i>I'm not making any excuses,</i>

274
00:17:30,091 --> 00:17:33,636
<i>because I aided and abetted</i>
<i>the worst crime of them all.</i>

275
00:17:35,304 --> 00:17:38,849
I personally drove
Special Agent Ben Poindexter

276
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:43,354
to the Clinton Church...
dressed in a fake Daredevil suit.

277
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,024
I knew at this point

278
00:17:47,108 --> 00:17:50,111
that Poindexter was the killer
who attacked the <i>Bulletin,</i>

279
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:53,155
<i>and I knew he was going to do</i>
<i>something horrible at the church.</i>

280
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:55,032
<i>But I let it happen anyway.</i>

281
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:04,333
So I'm guilty of aiding and abetting
the murder of Father Paul Lantom.

282
00:18:05,459 --> 00:18:07,128
<i>I'm ashamed of what I've done.</i>

283
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:10,006
<i>But that doesn't change the fact that I</i>

284
00:18:10,673 --> 00:18:13,593
and everyone I just named
are guilty as hell.

285
00:18:15,386 --> 00:18:16,220
Seems...

286
00:18:18,556 --> 00:18:20,474
<i>you need to get this video</i>
<i>to my attorneys.</i>

287
00:18:20,558 --> 00:18:22,351
<i>And don't try and run.</i>

288
00:18:22,977 --> 00:18:27,273
Go to the FBI and pretend like you
don't know anything about any of this.

289
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:29,775
Tell them I'm a monster.

290
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:34,113
[sobs] It's the only way that you and Sami
can get through this.

291
00:18:35,323 --> 00:18:36,866
<i>I'm sorry, baby.</i>

292
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,452
I will always love you.

293
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,204
[kisses]

294
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:47,918
-[exhales]
-[Karen] God.

295
00:18:51,005 --> 00:18:52,506
He knew he was gonna die.

296
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:57,011
Okay, so...
maybe it won't hold up in court.

297
00:18:57,094 --> 00:18:59,639
But if we put this out there,
it'll make Fisk's life a living hell.

298
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:05,186
Actually, a dying declaration
is exempt from the hearsay rule.

299
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:06,354
What?

300
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:09,899
The court says that a person
who believes that they're dying is...

301
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:11,567
has less incentive to lie.

302
00:19:11,651 --> 00:19:13,110
Therefore, anything they say is--

303
00:19:13,194 --> 00:19:15,196
You're telling me
this is admissible in court?

304
00:19:15,279 --> 00:19:16,989
Every damn word.

305
00:19:17,073 --> 00:19:18,908
It's the silver bullet to take down Fisk.

306
00:19:18,991 --> 00:19:21,160
Shit. The world has to know.

307
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:23,204
The world and Matt.

308
00:19:45,643 --> 00:19:47,603
[door lock clanking]

309
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:00,718
[Dex exclaims]

310
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:03,304
[Dex grunting]

311
00:21:06,015 --> 00:21:07,224
[Dex moaning]

312
00:21:09,185 --> 00:21:12,062
[breathing heavily and grunting]

313
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:24,825
[cell phone vibrating]

314
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:36,295
When I find you...

315
00:21:37,004 --> 00:21:40,841
[Matt over cell phone] <i>Like I said,</i>
<i>Fisk killed her and we both know it.</i>

316
00:21:40,925 --> 00:21:42,968
<i>-You did this.</i>
-Think, Dex.

317
00:21:44,178 --> 00:21:45,888
Who got Julie the job in the hotel?

318
00:21:46,597 --> 00:21:48,432
<i>Who had you followed</i>
<i>when you were stalking her?</i>

319
00:21:48,516 --> 00:21:50,476
<i>It was all Fisk.</i>

320
00:21:51,936 --> 00:21:53,896
You let him turn you into a murderer.

321
00:21:53,979 --> 00:21:56,023
You think he's gonna let
Julie get in the way?

322
00:21:58,192 --> 00:21:59,652
Why are you telling me this?

323
00:22:00,820 --> 00:22:02,905
'Cause Fisk wants to get married tonight.

324
00:22:04,073 --> 00:22:06,992
And I don't think he deserves
a life of happily ever after.

325
00:22:08,369 --> 00:22:09,912
[soft droning]

326
00:22:32,643 --> 00:22:34,270
[woman] Wonder what
the bride's gonna wear.

327
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:35,479
[man] Ladies and gentlemen,

328
00:22:35,563 --> 00:22:39,567
please have your invitations in hand
as you go through the metal detector.

329
00:22:40,693 --> 00:22:42,361
Who does Fisk think he is?

330
00:22:43,028 --> 00:22:45,698
Summoning us here with no notice.

331
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:48,409
Well, he's the only one who can.

332
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:51,036
Well, he's really starting to piss me off.

333
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:53,122
Oh, relax. Here, have some champagne.

334
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:55,416
You'll live longer.

335
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:59,920
-This is what we're running?
-[woman] Mmm-hmm.

336
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:07,720
Well, it's official. Yesterday sucked.

337
00:23:08,971 --> 00:23:10,097
Yes, it did.

338
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:13,058
But today is gonna make it all worth it.

339
00:23:13,142 --> 00:23:14,685
-What's this?
-Look.

340
00:23:17,813 --> 00:23:20,900
<i>My name is Special Agent Ray Nadeem</i>
<i>of the FBI,</i>

341
00:23:21,692 --> 00:23:22,902
<i>and under federal law,</i>

342
00:23:22,985 --> 00:23:25,613
<i>I swear that the testimony</i>
<i>I'm about to give...</i>

343
00:23:26,780 --> 00:23:28,532
[siren wailing]

344
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:36,790
[knocking on window]

345
00:23:36,874 --> 00:23:39,793
Parking's on 53rd.
We're staging the motorcade... Jesus.

346
00:23:39,877 --> 00:23:41,003
Hey there, Lim.

347
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:43,339
Dex?

348
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:49,094
That's Agent Lim.
He's one of the good ones.

349
00:23:49,178 --> 00:23:51,513
-What in the hell--
-Do yourself a favor.

350
00:23:52,473 --> 00:23:54,516
Walk away.

351
00:23:56,477 --> 00:23:57,937
[Lim grunting]

352
00:24:00,356 --> 00:24:02,316
[cardinal] ...to be a loving
and faithful husband,

353
00:24:02,399 --> 00:24:05,319
in plenty and in want,
in joy and in sorrow,

354
00:24:05,402 --> 00:24:09,365
in sickness and in health,
as long as you both shall live?

355
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:13,994
Wilson?

356
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:16,872
Wilson?

357
00:24:18,624 --> 00:24:19,500
I...

358
00:24:21,251 --> 00:24:22,419
Repeat the question.

359
00:24:22,503 --> 00:24:23,837
[crowd chuckling]

360
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:25,631
[cardinal] Do you?

361
00:24:28,092 --> 00:24:29,093
I do.

362
00:24:30,219 --> 00:24:32,179
-[cardinal] And you?
-I do.

363
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:34,723
Then you may.

364
00:24:40,813 --> 00:24:43,148
[crowd cheering]

365
00:25:06,046 --> 00:25:09,174
[announcer] ...we are so glad you could
come and celebrate with us tonight.

366
00:25:09,258 --> 00:25:13,387
It is my honor and privilege
to present to you for the first time...

367
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:17,057
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson Fisk.

368
00:25:23,689 --> 00:25:25,649
-Hi.
-Beautiful ceremony, Vanessa.

369
00:25:25,733 --> 00:25:26,942
Thank you for coming.

370
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:32,865
That was a bold move

371
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:35,743
to sit me next to the prosecutor
who tried to send me away.

372
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:38,162
I told him to hold my purse.

373
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:40,581
That must have been
very satisfying for you.

374
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:43,667
It was. My tax dollars at work.

375
00:25:44,460 --> 00:25:45,836
You never disappoint.

376
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:48,005
[announcer] And now, ladies and gentlemen,

377
00:25:48,088 --> 00:25:52,384
we'd like to invite the bride and groom
to the floor for the first dance.

378
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:53,719
I believe that's our cue.

379
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:55,804
[music playing]

380
00:26:21,288 --> 00:26:23,749
[indistinct chatter]

381
00:26:33,092 --> 00:26:34,343
[cell phones chime]

382
00:26:36,053 --> 00:26:39,264
<i>My name is Special Agent Ray Nadeem</i>
<i>of the FBI,</i>

383
00:26:39,807 --> 00:26:41,183
<i>and under federal law,</i>

384
00:26:41,892 --> 00:26:44,394
<i>I swear that the testimony</i>
<i>I'm about to give...</i>

385
00:26:45,312 --> 00:26:46,563
Everyone's looking at us.

386
00:26:50,109 --> 00:26:51,193
They're staring.

387
00:26:52,528 --> 00:26:53,737
[crowd murmuring]

388
00:26:53,821 --> 00:26:57,783
[Ray over recording] <i>...of criminal acts,</i>
<i>and I was in no way acting alone.</i>

389
00:26:57,866 --> 00:27:00,119
<i>Wilson Fisk coerced me...</i>

390
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:05,165
<i>My name is Special Agent Ray Nadeem</i>
<i>of the FBI...</i>

391
00:27:05,249 --> 00:27:06,250
What's happening?

392
00:27:06,333 --> 00:27:09,753
<i>...to extort protection money</i>
<i>from New York crime organizations.</i>

393
00:27:09,837 --> 00:27:11,713
<i>Agents Arinori...</i>

394
00:27:11,797 --> 00:27:14,091
[announcer] Ladies and gentlemen,
this next one's a favorite,

395
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:16,844
so grab your dance partner
and head to the floor.

396
00:27:18,929 --> 00:27:21,014
You'll handle it, Wilson.

397
00:27:21,557 --> 00:27:25,185
Like you handle everything.
Show them that none of it matters.

398
00:27:31,984 --> 00:27:34,695
[officer] Agents down.
Repeat, agents down.

399
00:27:35,279 --> 00:27:37,239
Daredevil is en route to the ballroom.

400
00:27:42,744 --> 00:27:44,663
Sir, there's trouble. Agents are down.

401
00:27:46,373 --> 00:27:47,666
We're under attack.

402
00:27:47,749 --> 00:27:49,668
-[microphone feedback]
-[music stops]

403
00:27:49,751 --> 00:27:51,211
-I'd like to make a toast.
-[crowd gasps]

404
00:27:51,295 --> 00:27:53,046
-[glass breaking]
-[woman] It's Daredevil.

405
00:27:54,298 --> 00:27:57,217
Julie and I wish you the absolute best.

406
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:01,221
[crowd screaming]

407
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:20,866
[officer] Hold your fire!

408
00:28:24,161 --> 00:28:26,914
-How did this happen?
-Dex knows our security protocols.

409
00:28:28,916 --> 00:28:31,543
That video of Agent Nadeem
is a threat to us.

410
00:28:31,627 --> 00:28:34,922
I'll discredit his testimony
and take care of everything.

411
00:28:35,005 --> 00:28:36,215
-I will handle it.
-Wilson.

412
00:28:36,298 --> 00:28:38,467
I should have never let Dex
get that close to you.

413
00:28:38,550 --> 00:28:40,469
Be angry later. Be smart now.

414
00:28:41,011 --> 00:28:42,054
Listen to me.

415
00:28:46,016 --> 00:28:47,351
We need to run.

416
00:28:49,186 --> 00:28:51,563
You didn't make a mistake marrying me.

417
00:28:51,647 --> 00:28:54,107
I know that. But now, be smart.

418
00:28:54,816 --> 00:28:56,068
For both of us.

419
00:28:57,152 --> 00:28:58,028
[officers groaning]

420
00:29:24,137 --> 00:29:25,472
Please don't.

421
00:29:26,556 --> 00:29:27,641
[gun clicks]

422
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:39,569
Reports of Daredevil attacking the hotel
continue to circulate.

423
00:29:39,653 --> 00:29:42,322
Meanwhile, more and more police
are arriving at the scene.

424
00:29:42,406 --> 00:29:46,243
[Brett] ESU, you have one job:
Find and stop Daredevil.

425
00:29:46,326 --> 00:29:49,121
The rest of you,
we don't know which FBI agents

426
00:29:49,204 --> 00:29:51,581
-Fisk has in his pocket, so...
-Sure hope this wasn't Matt.

427
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:55,335
[all grunting]

428
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:03,677
You came back.

429
00:30:04,386 --> 00:30:07,055
Police are on their way up.
Can you shut down the elevators?

430
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:10,017
-[Shelby] Why?
-So nobody stops me.

431
00:30:26,450 --> 00:30:27,659
It's over.

432
00:30:28,243 --> 00:30:29,244
Run.

433
00:30:38,545 --> 00:30:41,340
[both screaming]

434
00:30:42,549 --> 00:30:43,633
[glass breaking]

435
00:31:09,409 --> 00:31:10,369
[exclaims]

436
00:31:23,924 --> 00:31:24,841
[screams]

437
00:32:23,650 --> 00:32:25,694
-What about you?
-Keep it, please.

438
00:32:30,365 --> 00:32:32,742
I'll meet you downstairs. Go!

439
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:12,115
[panting]

440
00:33:28,298 --> 00:33:30,133
[both yelling]

441
00:33:53,698 --> 00:33:54,616
[softly] Stop.

442
00:34:02,916 --> 00:34:04,584
Stop it, please!

443
00:34:11,132 --> 00:34:14,553
[screaming]

444
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:22,394
I will never stop hunting Karen Page
or Foggy Nelson.

445
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,856
I will tell the world who you really are.

446
00:34:27,899 --> 00:34:28,858
Wilson.

447
00:34:28,942 --> 00:34:31,903
Vanessa, please go. Please!

448
00:34:33,113 --> 00:34:35,156
[grunting] You...

449
00:34:35,240 --> 00:34:36,950
You want me to kill you.

450
00:34:37,033 --> 00:34:38,868
No prison can keep me.

451
00:34:39,452 --> 00:34:40,328
You know that.

452
00:34:40,829 --> 00:34:43,582
-Come on, kill me!
-[Matt] No!

453
00:34:43,665 --> 00:34:47,877
God knows I want to,
but you don't get to destroy who I am.

454
00:34:48,461 --> 00:34:49,921
You will go back to prison,

455
00:34:50,005 --> 00:34:53,550
and you will live the rest
of your miserable life in a cage,

456
00:34:53,633 --> 00:34:56,386
knowing you'll never have Vanessa,

457
00:34:56,469 --> 00:34:59,264
that this city rejected you.

458
00:34:59,347 --> 00:35:00,599
It beat you.

459
00:35:00,682 --> 00:35:03,143
I beat you!

460
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:10,275
You'll keep my secret,

461
00:35:11,276 --> 00:35:14,821
and you won't harm Karen Page
or Foggy Nelson

462
00:35:14,904 --> 00:35:16,156
or anyone else.

463
00:35:17,115 --> 00:35:21,036
Because if you do,
I will go after your wife.

464
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:22,495
[Fisk snarls softly]

465
00:35:23,705 --> 00:35:27,834
And I will prove Vanessa ordered
the murder of Agent Ray Nadeem,

466
00:35:28,710 --> 00:35:30,086
and like her husband,

467
00:35:30,170 --> 00:35:32,839
she'll spend the rest of her life
in a cell.

468
00:35:39,554 --> 00:35:42,307
I failed you. I failed you.

469
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:43,475
No.

470
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:45,602
[Fisk] Everything that I tried
to build for us...

471
00:35:49,356 --> 00:35:50,357
Vanessa...

472
00:35:53,360 --> 00:35:55,779
today was the happiest day of my life.

473
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,500
All I wanted was you.

474
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:11,169
Please.

475
00:36:24,557 --> 00:36:28,311
If I agree to your demands, then...

476
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:31,731
you leave my wife alone.

477
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,901
You leave Vanessa free!

478
00:36:41,408 --> 00:36:42,951
If you keep your word.

479
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:51,418
Then, it's a deal.

480
00:36:56,339 --> 00:36:57,465
[banging on door]

481
00:37:04,180 --> 00:37:05,807
[officers yelling indistinctly]

482
00:37:18,445 --> 00:37:21,698
Wilson Fisk, you are under arrest.

483
00:37:25,034 --> 00:37:26,911
[Dex] I can't move.

484
00:37:28,204 --> 00:37:29,539
He isn't the real Daredevil.

485
00:37:30,165 --> 00:37:31,332
[officer] How do you know?

486
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,293
Because he is.

487
00:37:39,090 --> 00:37:41,468
[indistinct chatter]

488
00:37:53,813 --> 00:37:55,732
-He's alive.
-[Karen sighs]

489
00:37:56,983 --> 00:37:58,026
Thank God.

490
00:38:08,661 --> 00:38:11,164
Please, give me a moment
to say goodbye to my wife.

491
00:38:12,081 --> 00:38:14,167
-Did you give one to Ray Nadeem?
-[Fisk] Please.

492
00:38:17,128 --> 00:38:18,797
[screaming]

493
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:20,423
Please!

494
00:38:32,894 --> 00:38:34,312
Matt should be here.

495
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:38,525
Well, I'm pretty sure he is.

496
00:39:28,491 --> 00:39:30,994
Last time we spoke,
I confronted Father Lantom.

497
00:39:33,162 --> 00:39:34,247
I was angry.

498
00:39:35,790 --> 00:39:37,166
I'd change that if I could.

499
00:39:37,876 --> 00:39:40,753
If God allowed that, there'd be no future.

500
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:44,799
-Just people endlessly rewriting the past.
-Yeah.

501
00:39:46,968 --> 00:39:49,387
I think he was trying to tell me that
for a long time.

502
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:55,560
His last words were, "Forgive us."

503
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,149
Do you think that's possible?

504
00:40:10,241 --> 00:40:14,495
He told me something, years ago,
when this happened, that I never forgot.

505
00:40:16,706 --> 00:40:21,419
See, I was pretty angry at God
and bitter towards his world.

506
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:26,215
How could a loving God blind me?

507
00:40:28,593 --> 00:40:29,594
Why?

508
00:40:30,595 --> 00:40:36,309
Anyway, he told me...
God's plan is like a beautiful tapestry.

509
00:40:37,185 --> 00:40:41,022
And the tragedy of being human is
that we only get to see it from the back.

510
00:40:42,523 --> 00:40:45,526
With all the ragged threads
and the muddy colors.

511
00:40:45,610 --> 00:40:49,447
And we only get a hint at the true beauty

512
00:40:49,530 --> 00:40:53,534
that would be revealed if we could see
the whole pattern on the other side...

513
00:40:55,203 --> 00:40:56,496
as God does.

514
00:41:00,375 --> 00:41:02,961
Anyway, I've been thinking
a lot about it recently, 'cause...

515
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:05,588
I realize I've made some bad choices

516
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:08,675
and hurt people
that I love without meaning to.

517
00:41:08,758 --> 00:41:11,302
You don't always know
when you start down a false path.

518
00:41:11,386 --> 00:41:13,972
No, you don't. And that's my point.

519
00:41:15,431 --> 00:41:18,184
I realize that if my life
had turned out any differently,

520
00:41:18,267 --> 00:41:20,186
that I would never have become Daredevil.

521
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:24,524
And although people have died on my watch,
people who shouldn't have,

522
00:41:25,191 --> 00:41:26,985
there are countless others
that have lived.

523
00:41:31,155 --> 00:41:35,118
So, maybe it is all part of God's plan.

524
00:41:38,705 --> 00:41:41,708
Maybe my life
has been exactly as it had to be.

525
00:41:46,421 --> 00:41:48,381
You have a generous heart, Matthew.

526
00:41:48,464 --> 00:41:49,632
[Matt chuckles softly]

527
00:41:50,591 --> 00:41:52,510
To see the good in so much pain.

528
00:41:53,469 --> 00:41:54,637
Not always.

529
00:41:58,266 --> 00:42:00,810
In fact, Father Lantom
used to help me with that.

530
00:42:02,603 --> 00:42:05,440
Help me see the errors of my ways.

531
00:42:09,110 --> 00:42:12,155
I could use someone else
to help me with that now...

532
00:42:14,490 --> 00:42:15,742
once in a while.

533
00:42:19,829 --> 00:42:21,289
I'm a nun, Matthew.

534
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:26,210
Helping is what I was called to do.

535
00:42:30,965 --> 00:42:33,259
[breathes deeply]

536
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:14,801
Feels like half of Hell's Kitchen
is here today

537
00:43:15,843 --> 00:43:18,179
to say goodbye to Father Paul Lantom.

538
00:43:19,597 --> 00:43:20,640
Seems fair.

539
00:43:21,849 --> 00:43:24,852
He certainly welcomed everyone here,
Catholic or not.

540
00:43:26,312 --> 00:43:28,356
And he expected those of us who were

541
00:43:28,439 --> 00:43:31,984
to, uh, look for ways to do good
in our community.

542
00:43:33,569 --> 00:43:35,613
Not even the kids
got out of that requirement.

543
00:43:36,155 --> 00:43:39,158
I'm sure I'm not the only one
who remembers his "suggestion"

544
00:43:39,242 --> 00:43:43,538
that we give some of our
First Communion money to the poor box.

545
00:43:43,621 --> 00:43:45,665
-[crowd chuckling]
-[Matt] And that was his way.

546
00:43:46,874 --> 00:43:50,878
To think of the community,
and the, uh... and the individuals in it.

547
00:43:52,630 --> 00:43:54,632
To think in terms of, "What can I give?"

548
00:43:55,174 --> 00:43:58,928
He gave his life, right here
in this church, protecting others.

549
00:44:00,721 --> 00:44:02,974
Standing up to a man who used fear

550
00:44:03,057 --> 00:44:05,434
as a tool to set neighbors
against one another.

551
00:44:06,936 --> 00:44:09,981
If Father Lantom had an enemy,
I would say it was fear.

552
00:44:12,859 --> 00:44:16,320
For me, personally, he spent many years
trying to get me to face my own fears.

553
00:44:17,113 --> 00:44:18,865
To understand how they enslaved me,

554
00:44:18,948 --> 00:44:21,868
how they divided me
from the people that I love.

555
00:44:22,785 --> 00:44:24,745
He counseled me to transcend my fears,

556
00:44:26,038 --> 00:44:27,707
to be brave enough to forgive...

557
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:32,670
and see the possibilities
of being a man without fear.

558
00:44:34,547 --> 00:44:35,798
That was his legacy.

559
00:44:38,926 --> 00:44:41,762
And now it's up to all of us
to, uh, live up to it.

560
00:44:45,141 --> 00:44:47,143
[indistinct chatter]

561
00:44:50,479 --> 00:44:51,439
[Matt sighs]

562
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:57,445
That was nice, what you said.

563
00:44:58,946 --> 00:45:01,324
[Matt] Yeah, it wasn't just him, you know.

564
00:45:03,117 --> 00:45:04,243
It was you, too.

565
00:45:06,078 --> 00:45:08,456
You helped me see the truth about myself.

566
00:45:11,042 --> 00:45:13,044
Ouch. That had to hurt.

567
00:45:13,127 --> 00:45:14,086
[chuckles]

568
00:45:15,004 --> 00:45:17,465
Well, maybe one of these days,
I'll forgive you, too.

569
00:45:17,548 --> 00:45:18,382
[Karen chuckles]

570
00:45:19,425 --> 00:45:21,219
Before my funeral, I hope.

571
00:45:23,054 --> 00:45:24,722
I'm glad you told me, Karen.

572
00:45:26,307 --> 00:45:28,684
About Wesley and your brother.

573
00:45:30,269 --> 00:45:31,270
Yeah.

574
00:45:31,938 --> 00:45:32,939
Well, uh...

575
00:45:34,607 --> 00:45:36,525
I couldn't live with that lie forever.

576
00:45:37,735 --> 00:45:40,154
We're all just trying to do
more good than harm.

577
00:45:41,072 --> 00:45:43,115
And I'd say you're ahead on that score.

578
00:45:51,666 --> 00:45:54,794
I was starting to like the idea
of being married to the DA.

579
00:45:55,962 --> 00:45:57,880
Pretty sure Blake Tower's not married.

580
00:45:58,297 --> 00:46:00,216
Yeah, he'll have to get by without me.

581
00:46:01,425 --> 00:46:03,261
You, on the other hand, are in luck.

582
00:46:03,636 --> 00:46:05,763
The firm will be thrilled
to have you back.

583
00:46:06,806 --> 00:46:08,557
The thing is, Marci...

584
00:46:09,475 --> 00:46:11,143
I'm not sure I want that anymore.

585
00:46:12,603 --> 00:46:15,106
I was afraid you were going to say
something like that.

586
00:46:16,649 --> 00:46:17,733
You're not mad?

587
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:20,486
We'll talk about it later.

588
00:46:21,028 --> 00:46:23,864
But do I really have to watch you
drive your campaign off a cliff?

589
00:46:24,282 --> 00:46:26,242
Nah. I got that part covered.

590
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:28,411
...that Wilson Fisk is a malignant tumor.

591
00:46:28,953 --> 00:46:31,747
Well, the State of New York
isn't going to make the same mistake.

592
00:46:31,831 --> 00:46:36,168
Everyone knows his game now.
Fisk won't manipulate the system again.

593
00:46:36,961 --> 00:46:39,213
Excuse me, Mr. Tower.

594
00:46:39,755 --> 00:46:40,798
[Tower] Mr. Nelson.

595
00:46:43,968 --> 00:46:45,886
I wanted you to be the first to hear

596
00:46:45,970 --> 00:46:49,181
that I'm officially dropping out
of the race for district attorney.

597
00:46:50,850 --> 00:46:54,145
The way you stood up to Wilson Fisk
was an inspiration to us all.

598
00:46:55,146 --> 00:46:56,814
I'm gonna be voting for you.

599
00:46:56,897 --> 00:46:59,358
Thank you. [chuckles]

600
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:06,615
-Hey there, Matty!
-[Matt] Uncle Timmy.

601
00:47:06,699 --> 00:47:09,744
-How are those briefs doing?
-Still stapled together.

602
00:47:09,827 --> 00:47:11,287
[laughs] Attaboy.

603
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:15,833
Of course, we're gonna
have to buy sunscreen by the bucket.

604
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:17,793
Better than that rock salt.

605
00:47:17,877 --> 00:47:20,755
Enough with the snow and ice.
We're getting out of here.

606
00:47:20,838 --> 00:47:22,840
I can't believe you're finally doing it.

607
00:47:22,923 --> 00:47:27,386
Guess I'll have to get used to the idea
of Christmas in Tampa. Yikes!

608
00:47:27,470 --> 00:47:29,889
Like I'd miss the grandkids at Christmas.

609
00:47:29,972 --> 00:47:31,640
-Speaking of which...
-Hold that thought.

610
00:47:31,724 --> 00:47:33,559
I need to talk to Theo for a minute.

611
00:47:36,645 --> 00:47:39,607
-You know she ain't giving up.
-You don't have to, either.

612
00:47:40,232 --> 00:47:42,777
Me? I don't even have a girlfriend.

613
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:46,322
I mean on this place.
Tower's taking down Red Lion Bank.

614
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:48,032
You talked to him?

615
00:47:48,699 --> 00:47:52,370
He's not going to prosecute a sweet
old couple who got screwed by Fisk.

616
00:47:53,579 --> 00:47:54,747
You, though...

617
00:47:55,498 --> 00:47:56,874
What about me?

618
00:47:56,957 --> 00:47:58,334
If you pay back the loan...

619
00:47:59,668 --> 00:48:01,253
they won't file criminal charges.

620
00:48:01,337 --> 00:48:02,505
[Theo exhales and chuckles]

621
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:06,675
That's some fancy lawyering, Foggy.
You're really saving my ass.

622
00:48:07,259 --> 00:48:10,179
Eh. Who wanted to be DA anyway?

623
00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:11,847
You're too good-looking for that job.

624
00:48:11,931 --> 00:48:12,765
Ow!

625
00:48:13,307 --> 00:48:14,725
So, what are you gonna do now?

626
00:48:15,393 --> 00:48:16,519
Drink these.

627
00:48:17,269 --> 00:48:18,270
Good plan.

628
00:48:20,773 --> 00:48:22,024
Is that a whiskey neat?

629
00:48:23,818 --> 00:48:25,903
-For medicinal purposes.
-[Karen] Mmm-hmm.

630
00:48:27,822 --> 00:48:29,323
You want me to get you your own?

631
00:48:30,074 --> 00:48:32,201
-Oh, this one tastes fine.
-[Matt chuckles]

632
00:48:32,284 --> 00:48:34,495
-Give Matt his drink back.
-Yes.

633
00:48:36,705 --> 00:48:41,168
So, I guess you guys heard,
Special Agent in Charge Hattley flipped.

634
00:48:41,710 --> 00:48:44,588
-She corroborated Ray's dying declaration.
-I did hear.

635
00:48:44,672 --> 00:48:45,506
[Karen] Hmm.

636
00:48:46,298 --> 00:48:49,969
So, the FBI is getting an enema,
and Fisk is...

637
00:48:50,928 --> 00:48:54,140
-still breathing.
-Yep. Still breathing.

638
00:48:54,682 --> 00:48:56,976
Headed to prison. Again.

639
00:48:57,059 --> 00:48:59,186
Not exactly what I had in mind.

640
00:49:00,479 --> 00:49:02,189
You trust that he'll keep his word?

641
00:49:02,815 --> 00:49:04,984
I mean, I trust that he loves Vanessa.

642
00:49:05,776 --> 00:49:08,654
Long as she's free, he should stay away.

643
00:49:08,737 --> 00:49:12,366
-And if she gets hit by a bus tomorrow?
-Yeah. Well, then we'll cross that bridge.

644
00:49:14,368 --> 00:49:17,621
So, how long you gonna stick around?

645
00:49:19,248 --> 00:49:23,127
Actually, I was thinking
about moving back into my apartment.

646
00:49:23,210 --> 00:49:24,211
Really?

647
00:49:24,295 --> 00:49:26,881
Well, seeing as the bills are paid,
I might as well.

648
00:49:26,964 --> 00:49:29,717
[chuckles] Okay, so hold on.
You're going to move

649
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:33,137
-back into Matt Murdock's apartment?
-[Matt] Yeah, yeah.

650
00:49:33,679 --> 00:49:36,390
I just figured he has
a healthier life-work balance.

651
00:49:36,474 --> 00:49:37,641
[Karen] Hmm?

652
00:49:37,725 --> 00:49:40,436
And... actual friends.

653
00:49:40,519 --> 00:49:43,606
Doesn't have a job, though.
He's kind of a mooch.

654
00:49:44,398 --> 00:49:45,858
Semi-decent lawyer, though.

655
00:49:45,941 --> 00:49:47,943
Ooh... "Semi-decent"? Ouch.

656
00:49:48,027 --> 00:49:51,197
[chuckles] You do break the law.
A lot. And often.

657
00:49:51,280 --> 00:49:54,116
Objection. Sustained.

658
00:49:55,826 --> 00:49:59,121
I have a crazy idea. I need a new napkin.

659
00:50:04,168 --> 00:50:08,881
-Okay. Well, he's writing something.
-Apparently.

660
00:50:15,262 --> 00:50:16,263
[Matt] What?

661
00:50:18,015 --> 00:50:21,352
Oh, he just wrote
all of our names, didn't he?

662
00:50:21,435 --> 00:50:22,937
How can you know that?

663
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:26,357
-'Cause I was thinking the same thing.
-Okay. Okay, guys, I'm not a lawyer.

664
00:50:27,441 --> 00:50:29,109
You're one hell of an investigator.

665
00:50:29,193 --> 00:50:31,737
Yeah, and way more stable
than Jessica Jones.

666
00:50:31,820 --> 00:50:33,948
[all chuckling]

667
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:35,616
All right, so what? What does that mean?

668
00:50:35,699 --> 00:50:38,452
We go back to helping people
out of a crappy office,

669
00:50:38,536 --> 00:50:39,954
getting paid in chickens?

670
00:50:40,913 --> 00:50:43,040
I think Theo would let us
work out of here, to start.

671
00:50:43,123 --> 00:50:45,334
At least we'd have a place
to sell the chickens.

672
00:50:45,417 --> 00:50:46,669
[chuckles]

673
00:50:47,962 --> 00:50:49,630
-So what do you think?
-[Karen sighs]

674
00:50:52,800 --> 00:50:54,176
Why the hell not?

675
00:50:55,636 --> 00:50:57,638
To Nelson, Murdock & Page.

676
00:50:58,389 --> 00:51:01,058
-Page, Murdock & Nelson.
-Hang on a minute.

677
00:51:01,141 --> 00:51:02,726
That actually has a nice ring to it.

678
00:51:13,862 --> 00:51:16,574
[surgeon] Doctor, if this fails,
he'll be permanently paralyzed.

679
00:51:19,118 --> 00:51:20,869
T8 and T9 are falling apart.

680
00:51:21,495 --> 00:51:24,873
Even using cadaver material,
reconstruction is hopeless.

681
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:27,126
[doctor] I disagree.

682
00:51:28,586 --> 00:51:31,297
The Cogmium steel
reinforcing framework is--

683
00:51:31,380 --> 00:51:34,216
[surgeon] Can't replace
pulverized vertebrae, Dr. Oyama.

684
00:51:34,967 --> 00:51:36,719
[Oyama] The patient knew the risks.

685
00:51:37,303 --> 00:51:38,304
We continue.

686
00:51:52,776 --> 00:51:54,194
[dramatic music playing]

